    <p class="text-gray-500 text-base mt-4 leading-relaxed">
      You bought a 1 TB drive, plugged it in, and Windows reported 931 GB. Nothing was stolen and nothing is hidden — you're watching two counting systems describe the same bytes. This guide settles the gigabyte/gibibyte split properly: the exact definitions, the walkthrough of where "931" comes from, a decoder for every common drive size, and the table of which software counts which way — so the numbers never surprise you again.
    </p>

    <div class="mt-6 p-5 rounded-2xl bg-gradient-to-r from-indigo-50 to-white border-l-4 border-indigo-500">
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-700">By <a href="/about-us/" class="text-indigo-600 font-semibold hover:underline">Editorial Team</a></p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">📅 <strong class="text-gray-600">Published:</strong> July 31, 2026 &nbsp;|&nbsp; 🔄 <strong class="text-gray-600">Last reviewed:</strong> July 31, 2026</p>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mt-1">
